    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"750526\">Christian Poveda</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Can't.20find.20.60cty.60.20in.20bindings.2Ers/near/468149586\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>the builder struct has a method to add raw rust lines to the generated bindings. You could use that</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/35136/Mj4q2Gt3qTiDpANdbHMeSySW/image.png\">image.png</a> </p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/35136/Mj4q2Gt3qTiDpANdbHMeSySW/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img data-original-dimensions=\"3024x1890\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/35136/Mj4q2Gt3qTiDpANdbHMeSySW/image.png/840x560.webp\"></a></div><p>I added this line to my <a href=\"http://build.rs\">build.rs</a> - <code>.raw_line(\"extern crate cty;\")</code> </p>\n<p><a href=\"http://bindings.rs\">bindings.rs</a> include <code>extern crate cty;</code> now after I regenerated it.</p>\n<p>However <code>cty</code> can't be found still. Maybe it's about how I build my kernel module?</p>\n<p>This is the part of my Makefile (I build with <code>make LLVM=1 all</code>):</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Makefile\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nf\">bindings.rs</span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span>cargo<span class=\"w\"> </span>build<span class=\"w\"> </span>--release\n<span class=\"w\">    </span>find<span class=\"w\"> </span>target/release/build/<span class=\"w\"> </span>-name<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"bindings.rs\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-exec<span class=\"w\"> </span>cp<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>./<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\;</span>\n\n<span class=\"nf\">lib.o</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">lib</span>.<span class=\"n\">rs</span> <span class=\"n\">bindings</span>.<span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span>rustc<span class=\"w\"> </span>--crate-type<span class=\"w\"> </span>staticlib<span class=\"w\"> </span>--emit<span class=\"o\">=</span>obj<span class=\"w\"> </span>-o<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">$@</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>lib.rs\n\n<span class=\"nv\">obj-m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>ovpn_dco_rust.o\n<span class=\"nv\">ovpn_dco_rust-objs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>lib.o\n\n<span class=\"nv\">BUILD_FLAGS</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">M</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"k\">$(</span>PWD<span class=\"k\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">PWD</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"k\">$(</span>PWD<span class=\"k\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">REVISION</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"k\">$(</span>REVISION<span class=\"k\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">CONFIG_OVPN_DCO_V2</span><span class=\"o\">=</span>m<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">INSTALL_MOD_DIR</span><span class=\"o\">=</span>updates/\n\n<span class=\"nf\">all</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">config</span> <span class=\"n\">bindings</span>.<span class=\"n\">rs</span> <span class=\"n\">lib</span>.<span class=\"n\">o</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">$(</span>MAKE<span class=\"k\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-C<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">$(</span>KERNEL_SRC<span class=\"k\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">$(</span>BUILD_FLAGS<span class=\"k\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>modules\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 468151563,
        "sender_full_name": "Nikolai Shv",
        "timestamp": 1725620588
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>my guess is that you have to pass the library file for <code>cty</code> to <code>rustc</code> somehow, I'm not sure how's that handled in a kernel module.</p>\n<p>At the same time I'm not sure I understand why you need to use this <code>cty</code> crate, most of these types are already available in <code>core::ffi</code> aren't they?</p>",
        "id": 468367620,
        "sender_full_name": "Christian Poveda",
        "timestamp": 1725695728
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"750526\">Christian Poveda</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Can't.20find.20.60cty.60.20in.20bindings.2Ers/near/468367620\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>my guess is that you have to pass the library file for <code>cty</code> to <code>rustc</code> somehow, I'm not sure how's that handled in a kernel module.</p>\n<p>At the same time I'm not sure I understand why you need to use this <code>cty</code> crate, most of these types are already available in <code>core::ffi</code> aren't they?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>you're right, I'm using ::core</p>",
